com.samsung.android.sdk.healthdata

Interface HealthConstants.SleepStage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HealthConstants.Common, HealthConstants.SessionMeasurement
    Enclosing class:
    HealthConstants

    public static interface HealthConstants.SleepStage
extends HealthConstants.SessionMeasurement
    This interface defines the detailed sleep stage for the specified sleep data.

    Properties of the following extending interfaces are available for this data type.

    • HealthConstants.Common
    • HealthConstants.SessionMeasurement

    Sleep and Sleep Stage

    HealthConstants.Sleep includes only the start and end time of user's sleep. SleepStage gives detailed sleep stage information with several sections for the specified Sleep data.

    The sleep stage can be presented as the following figure.

    Sleep #1

    Sleep data is saved as "Sleep #1" if HealthConstants.Sleep is used only.

    Sleep #2

    Otherwise, "Sleep #2" data that is composed of HealthConstants.Sleep and HealthConstants.SleepStage.
    It shows:

    • User goes to bed at 23:30.
    • The user's sleep stage is SLEEP_LIGHT for 23:30 ~ 00:40 of the next day.
    • The user's sleep stage is SLEEP_DEEP for 00:40 ~ 02:00.
    • The user's sleep stage is SLEEP_REM for 02:00 ~ 05:10.
    • The user's sleep stage is SLEEP_AWAKE for 05:10 ~ 06:30.
    • User awakes at 06:30.

    Properties

    Sleep stage data has the following properties.
    See more common properties by spreading this section out.

      Property name Description
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.UUID [Mandatory]
      Data's unique ID,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.CREATE_TIME [Mandatory]
      Data's created time in the health data store,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.UPDATE_TIME [Mandatory]
      Data's updated time in the health data store,
      assigned by the system when new data is updated
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.PACKAGE_NAME [Mandatory]
      Application package name which provides data,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.DEVICE_UUID [Mandatory]
      Device identifier of the source device which provides health data
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.START_TIME [Mandatory]
      UTC Time when the measurement is started
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.END_TIME [Mandatory]
      UTC Time after the measurement has ended
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.TIME_OFFSET [Mandatory]
      Time offset which considers time zone and daylight saving time
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.SLEEP_ID [Mandatory]
      The specified sleep data's ID
      HealthConstants.SleepStage.STAGE [Mandatory]
      Sleep stage

    Data Permission

    Data permission acquisition for this data type is required toread or write data.
    See Permission Manager and request data permission.
    Since:
    1.2.0

        Deep stage of sleep.

        1.2.0

        static final int STAGE_REM
        REM (Rapid Eye Movement) stage of sleep.
